{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.16",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 16,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 16",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 16 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:2",
      "text": "I have heard many such things: poor comforters are ye all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:3",
      "text": "What! is there any reason in vain words? or what will hinder thee from answering?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:4",
      "text": "I also will speak as ye do: if indeed your soul were in my soul's stead, then would I insult you with words, and I would shake my head at you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:5",
      "text": "And would there were strength in my mouth, and I would not spare the movement of my lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:6",
      "text": "For if I should speak, I shall not feel the pain of my wound: and if I should be silent, how shall I be wounded the less?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:7",
      "text": "But now he has made me weary, and a worn-out fool; and thou hast laid hold of me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:8",
      "text": "My falsehood has become a testimony, and has risen up against me: it has confronted me to my face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:9",
      "text": "In his anger he has cast me down; he has gnashed his teeth upon me: the weapons of his robbers have fallen upon me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:10",
      "text": "He has attacked me with the keen glances of his eyes; with his sharp spear he has smitten me down upon my knees; and they have run upon me with one accord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:11",
      "text": "For the Lord has delivered me into the hands of unrighteous men, and thrown me upon the ungodly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:12",
      "text": "When I was at peace he distracted me: he took me by the hair of the head, and plucked it out: he set me up as a mark.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:13",
      "text": "They surrounded me with spears, aiming at my reins: without sparing me they poured out my gall upon the ground.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:14",
      "text": "They overthrew me with fall upon fall: they ran upon me in their might.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:15",
      "text": "They sewed sackcloth upon my skin, and my strength has been spent on the ground.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:16",
      "text": "My belly has been parched with wailing, and darkness is on my eyelids.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:17",
      "text": "Yet there was no injustice in my hands, and my prayer is pure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:18",
      "text": "Earth, cover not over the blood of my flesh, and let my cry have no place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:19",
      "text": "And now, behold, my witness is in heaven, and my advocate is on high.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:20",
      "text": "Let my supplication come to the Lord, and let mine eye weep before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:21",
      "text": "Oh that a man might plead before the Lord, even as the son of man with his neighbour!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.16.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:22",
      "text": "But my years are numbered and their end come, and I shall go by the way by which I shall not return.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
